column5: Been cleaning up my hobby area and I have a bunch of old fishing tackle, most of it needs cleaning up/painting/new hooks stuff like that (a couple of items might even be antiques) but instead of just throwing it away I thought I would offer it for free to anyone interested in it.Â  I might even dig out a few more items between now and someone claiming it.Â  That's a large size freezer bag BTW not a sandwich bag
Do you deliver? i would like these delivered ASAP!!!
For you my friend I sure would, Can I take you and MA out for dinner one evening this week?

Its a date. All kidding aside, the rod/reel combo would be a welcome addition to Seanâ€™s collection. The assorted tackle should go to someone who can repurpose it. I have tons of tackle still in original packaging and I would like to see it going to someone who will actually use it. Lots of great karma in that tackle
I'll bring the rod and reel with me when I come down on Saturday. I'll hold on to the tackle until I find a new home for it.
Is there an herb's dilly in there? If so, I know someone who would drag their bumÂ through 100 miles of broken glass to get their hands on it.
I have no idea what's in there but there are a few pretty old ones.

A good home has been found ğŸ˜Š. A lady that spends her summers fishing with her grand kids was more than happy to have my leftovers and I even managed to throw in a few little extras for the kids. Guess it's true, "one man's junk is another man's treasure"!
